The Buhari Media Organisa­tion (BMO) has expressed dis­appointment and condemna­tion over the sermon delivered by Bishop Matthew Kukah on Christmas Day 2020, where he made unfounded allegations against President Muhamma­du Buhar, and also made subtle calls for a coup in the country. The group, in a statement signed by its Chairman, Niyi Akinsiju and Secretary, Cassi­dy Madueke, noted that this was not the first time the Catholic Bishop had used the pulpit to sow discord and fuel an agenda of anarchy. “We condemn the remarks of Bishop Kukah where he made claims that the President was creating a northern hege­mony and that such could have been the reason for a coup. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “These comments are false, unreasonable and evil. They are anti-Nigeria and have no place in the kind of conversations Ni­gerians deserve to hear at a time that all are longing for peace and love. “Time after time, the Pres­ident Buhari administration has responded with clear facts, numbers and statistics on this allegation of nepotism, show­ing that in fact, the South-West has the most appointees in the government, while the South has more appointees than the North.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION